<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>DT-466E and 530E Diesel Engine Service (1995 through 1999) - SECTION 8: TIMING GEAR TRAIN AND FRONT COVER -
        GEAR TRAIN REMOVAL - IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLIES
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="2">
        <title>IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLIES</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the lower idler gear as follows. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk xrefid="ef1600819">8.19</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                :
            </para>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Loosen and remove the idler gear retaining bolt using idler gear socket
                    <emph type="bold">ZTSE4383</emph>.
                </para>
            </step2>
            <step2>
                <para count="1">Remove the idler gear assembly from the front cover.</para>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>A NEW UPPER IDLER GEAR BOLT MUST BE USED WITH EACH INSTALLATION OF THE UPPER IDLER GEAR.
                            THERE IS A PREAPPLIED SEALANT ON THE NEW MOUNTING BOLT.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <specpara>
                    <note>
                        <para>Each idler gear (upper and lower) are supported on tapered roller bearings and shafts. The
                            bearing retaining nut should not be removed as it is required for torquing the nut. If the
                            bearing is worn or loose, replace the complete gear assembly.
                        </para>
                    </note>
                </specpara>
                <figure id="ef1600818" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5310" filename="../figeg5/EG5310.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.18 Checking Camshaft End Play</caption>
                </figure>
                <figure id="ef1600819" figsize="col-wide">
                    <graphic id="eg5318" filename="../figeg5/EG5318.webp" type="webp"/>
                    <caption>Figure 8.19 Removing Lower Idler Gear</caption>
                </figure>
            </step2>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the upper idler gear as follows. Refer to
                <emph type="bold">Figure
                    <hotlnk document="e160_223.xml" xrefid="ef1600820">8.20</hotlnk>
                </emph>
                .
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the idler gear retaining bolt and
                <emph type="bold">DISCARD</emph>. Remove idler gear.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>A NEW UPPER IDLER GEAR BOLT MUST BE USED WITH EACH INSTALLATION OF THE UPPER IDLER GEAR. THERE
                        IS A PREAPPLIED SEALANT ON THE NEW MOUNTING BOLT.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Each idler gear (upper and lower) are supported on tapered roller bearings and shafts. The
                        bearing retaining nut should not be removed as it is required for torquing the nut. If the
                        bearing is worn or loose, replace the complete gear assembly.
                    </para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
